The paper discusses a framework for exploring the knowledge structure of multidisciplinary research fields using bibliographic data. This involves retrieving online bibliographic data and conducting longitudinal analyses to interpret and visualize the data. The paper does not focus on any specific computer science subfield, but rather presents a general approach that could be applied to various fields. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
